BIG day for menopause! 

#womenshealth #menopause #perimenopause

✨️ It's been four years since we started to think about changing the menopause narrative, and this week marks two years since we officially launched Alloy. Today, we’re celebrating this milestone and reflecting on the journey that got us here.

When we started building Alloy, we knew we wanted to call out the B.S. out there about menopause and rewrite the playbook. We wanted to help women understand their bodies and give them what they need to feel great, both mentally and physically, as they enter this next phase of life.

Since launch, we have improved the lives of thousands of women (and all the other people in their lives!) by providing access to safe and effective menopause treatment. 90% of our customers have told us they feel better within two weeks of starting treatment through Alloy. We hear from them all the time through our regular member support groups and expert webinars.

The progress we’ve made advancing the national conversation about menopause is beyond gratifying. The announcement of a new initiative focused on women's health and menopause research from the White House this week (finally!) is a testament to the leaps we've made.

We’re grateful to our doctors, our team, and our community. We know this is just the beginning. Here’s to more conversation, more support, and more heart–because feeling fantastic shouldn’t just be a dream.

Thanks for being along for the ride!

#AlloyWomensHealth #Alloy #MyAlloy #Menopause

Still feeling all warm and fuzzy after our most recent offsite! Here's a quick lil recap from @annefulenwider 

#Alloywomenshealth #MyAlloy #alloy
Here’s the bottom line: We trust you to make decisions about your own health. We’re here to help you make them based on FACTS, not fear.

What makes Alloy different? So many things! First, each of our founders comes to Alloy with her own story and her own experiences. It allows us to understand that while menopause only has one definition, there are SO many ways to go through it, and we treat it accordingly!

Second? We’re having fun! As Anne says, we’ll treat your symptoms but we’re also here to show you how truly wonderful this time can be!

Essential reading 📢 A critical review refuting the Women’s Heath Initiative was officially published in the Menopause Journal yesterday.

To quote one of our favorite parts:

"If the WHI had transparently reported their breast cancer findings in 2002, emphasizing, among other things, lack of statistical significance in breast cancer risk in the per-protocol adjusted statistic; had quickly followed up by publishing a per-protocol analysis adjusting for baseline breast cancer risk factors; and reminded the public that their findings did not apply to women initiating HT in perimenopause or early postmenopause, there would have been minimal controversy, no confusion, and women's health would not have suffered so dramatically over the ensuing decades."

🤯 Let that sink in. And then go grab some 🫖 and read the full article at the link in bio.
